                  <handDesc>
                     
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script">Mediocre, somewhat irregular</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black, red</seg>
                        The scribe's name <persName role="scribe" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS12924GabraMikaelScribe">Gabra Mikāʾel</persName> is written in the supplication formulas on <locus target="#63vb">63vb</locus>, 95ra, 118vb.
 The same scribe wrote Ms.

                           <ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESmkl012">MKL-012</ref>.<date notBefore="1800" notAfter="1900">19th century (?)</date>

                        <seg type="rubrication">Holy names; name of the protagonist; names of the
                           commissioners and the scribe; groups of lines (alternating with black
                           lines) on the incipit page of Text I; incipits of Texts II-III; incipits
                           of sections/miracles; elements of the punctuation signs; elements of
                           Ethiopic numerals.</seg>
                     </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <decoDesc>

                     <decoNote type="frame" xml:id="d1">
                        <locus target="#3r">3r</locus> (incipit of Text I): coloured (red, yellow)
                        ornamental band; geometric and floral motifs.</decoNote>
                     <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d2">
                        <locus target="#119v">Fol. 119v: </locus>
                        <desc>Virgin Mary with her Child, Archangels Michael and
                        Gabriel.</desc>Legend: ቅዱስ፡ ሚካኤል፡ ምስለ፡ ፍቁር፡ ወልዳ፡ ቅዱስ፡ ገብርኤል “Saint Michael
                        with Her beloved Son, Saint Gabriel”.</decoNote>
                     <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d3">
                        <locus target="#120r">Fol. 120r: </locus>
                        <desc>St. Gabra Manfas Qǝddus with lions and leopards.</desc>Legend: አቡነ፡
                        ገብረ፡ መንፈስ፡ ቅዱስ፡ ምስለ፡ አናብስት፡ ወአናምርት[sic] “ʾAbuna Gabra Manfas Qǝddus with
                        lions and leopards”.</decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus target="#119ra">f. 119ra</locus>
                           <desc type="ScribalNoteCommissioning">: Note on commissioning of the writing.</desc>
                           <q xml:lang="gez"/>
                           
                           <note> The note is written in the main hand. Walda Libānos and his wife
                              Fre Māryām are mentioned as the commissioners of the Ms. for their
                              children Ḫāyla Śǝllāse, ʾAmata Śǝllāse, Walatta Śǝllāse, Walatta Ṣǝyon
                              and for fathers Za-Walda Māryām and Mazgaba Śǝllāse (s. also Varia,
                              below). </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1"><desc>- Tamallas-sign in the shape of ┴ indicating the place
                           where the omission, written in the upper margin in the main hand,
                           belongs: <locus target="#105vb">105vb</locus> l.8.</desc></item>
                        <item xml:id="e2">
                           <desc>Three names,
                           Walda Yoḥannǝs, Takla Hāymānot and Gabra Māryām, are crudely written
                           under Additio 1, in the same hand as the monthly readings.</desc></item>
                        <item xml:id="e3">
                           <desc>Minor
                           notes, writing exercises, doodles: <locus target="#1r">1r</locus>, 2r,
                           121r.</desc></item>
                        <item xml:id="e4">
                           <desc type="findingAid">- Monthly readings of Text I are indicated by the
                              names of the months written in the upper margin, in the main hand:
                              ዘሚያዝያ: <locus target="#3ra">fol. 3ra</locus> ዘግንቦት: <locus target="#10rb">fol. 10rb</locus> ዘሰኔ: <locus target="#16ra">fol.
                                 16ra</locus> ዘሐምሌ: <locus target="#21vb">fol. 21vb</locus> ዘነሐሴ:
                                 <locus target="#27va">fol. 27va</locus> ዘመስከረም: <locus target="#35ra">fol. 35ra</locus> ዘጥቅምት: <locus target="#46va">fol.
                                 46va</locus> ዘኅዳር: <locus target="#55va">fol. 55va</locus> ዘታሕሣሥ:
                                 <locus target="#64rb">fol. 64rb</locus> ዘጥር: <locus target="#71rb">fol. 71rb</locus> ዘየካቲት: <locus target="#81vb">fol. 81vb</locus>
                              ዘመጋቢት: <locus target="#88rb">fol. 88rb</locus>. </desc></item>
                        <item xml:id="e5">
                           <desc type="findingAid">Monthly readings of
                              Text II are indicated by the names of the months crudely written in
                              the upper margin, in the same hand as that which wrote three names
                              below Additio 1: ዘሚያዝያ: <locus target="#95rb">fol. 95rb</locus> ዘግንቦት:
                                 <locus target="#97r">fol. 97r</locus> ዘሰኔ: <locus target="#98vb">fol. 98vb</locus> ዘሐምሌ: <locus target="#99vb">fol. 99vb</locus>
                              ዘነሐሴ: <locus target="#101va">fol. 101va</locus> ዘመስከረም: <locus target="#103vb">fol. 103vb</locus> ዘጥቅምት: <locus target="#104vb">fol. 104vb</locus> ዘኅዳር: <locus target="#106va">fol. 106va</locus>
                              ዘታሕሣሥ: <locus target="#107ra">fol. 107ra</locus> ዘጥር: <locus target="#109vb">fol. 109vb</locus> ዘየካቲት: <locus target="#112rb">fol. 112rb</locus> ዘመጋቢት: <locus target="#114vb">fol.
                                 114vb</locus>.</desc>
                        </item>
                     </list>
