                  <provenance>Walda Libānos and his wife Fre Māryām are
                     mentioned in Additio 1 as the commissioners of the Ms. for their children Ḫāyla
                     Śǝllāse, ʾAmata Śǝllāse, Walatta Śǝllāse and Walatta Ṣǝyon as well as for
                     fathers Zawalda Māryām and Mazgaba Śǝllāse. Their names are written in the
                     supplication formulas: Walda Libānos (e.g., <locus target="#3ra">3ra</locus>,
                     21va, 27rb, 55va, 63vb, 88rb, 103vb), Fre Māryām (e.g., <locus target="#21vb">21vb</locus>, 27rb, 55va, 63vb, 88rb 103vb), Ḫāyla Śǝllāse (e.g., <locus target="#27rb">27rb</locus>, 63vb, 88rb, 103vb),
                     ʾAmata Śǝllāse (e.g.,
                     <locus target="#63vb">63vb</locus>, 88rb, Walatta Śǝllāse (e.g., <locus target="#103vb">103vb</locus>), Walatta Ṣǝyon (e.g., <locus target="#95ra">95ra</locus>), 
                     Zawalda Māryām and Mazgaba Śǝllāse (e.g., <locus target="#81vb">81vb</locus>).</provenance>
               </history>
